## ğŸ”§ CI/CD Workflow

### 1. Build Stage  
Jenkins builds a Docker image from the Dockerfile.

### 2. Push Stage  
The pipeline pushes the image to DockerHub under the `tamarmey` repository.

### 3. Deploy Stage  
Jenkins triggers an Ansible playbook that:  
- Connects to Minikube via inventory  
- Applies Deployment, Service, and ConfigMap  
- Updates the Deployment with the latest image  
- Verifies rollout completion  

## â˜¸ï¸ Kubernetes Components

### Deployment (deployment.yaml)
- Manages pod replicas  
- Pulls the latest DockerHub image  
- Includes readiness & liveness probes  

### Service (service.yaml)
- Exposes the application internally or via NodePort  

### ConfigMap (configmap.yaml)
- Provides application environment variables  

## â–¶ï¸ Manual Run (Optional)

### Start Minikube:
minikube start

### Build image:
docker build -t hellok8s-ci2 .

### Apply manifests:
kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml  
kubectl apply -f service.yaml  
kubectl apply -f configmap.yaml  

### Check pods:
kubectl get pods

